lation%20of%20a%20large%2C%20complex%20and%20globally-integrated%20economy%20is%20costly%20and%20unattainable%2C%26quot%3B%20Elina%20Ribakova%20wrote%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F784eae1d-1fb8-455b-b3d3-2ddc4715499d%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20sweeping%20Western%20sanctions%20over%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20Russia%20posted%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftass.com%2Feconomy%2F1743227%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGDP%20growth%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%203.6%25%20in%202023%20after%20contracting%201.2%25%20in%202022.%20The%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imf.org%2Fen%2FCountries%2FRUS%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EInternational%20Monetary%20Fund%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20expects%20the%20economy%20to%20continue%20growing%20and%20rise%202.6%25%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20economy%20has%20managed%20to%20keep%20humming%20because%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-putin-preparing-west-sanctions-decade-since-ukraine-crimea-annexation-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreparing%20for%20sanctions%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%202014.%20Moscow%20and%20Beijing%20have%20also%20launched%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-russia-alternative-swift-payment-cips-spfs-yuan-ruble-dollar-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealternative%20payments%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20skirt%20the%20widely%20used%20SWIFT%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20official%20statistics%20from%20Russia%20should%20be%20%26quot%3Bapproached%20with%20caution%2C%26quot%3B%20Ribakova%20said%20the%20country's%20economy%20appears%20to%20have%20stabilized%20thanks%20to%20wartime%20spending.%20The%20West%20has%20also%20not%20stopped%20completely%20b