22_blank%5C%22%3Eskip%20the%20hassles%20of%20security%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20crowded%20passenger%20terminals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20choice%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20business%20planes%2C%20with%20everything%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-see-inside-the-5-million-hondajet-that-costs-4k-an-hour-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmaller%20HondaJet%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20massive%20Bombardier%20Global%207500%20on%20the%20market.%20The%20latter%20typically%20comes%20complete%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsee-inside-the-75-million-bombardier-global-7500-private-jet-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebedroom%20and%20entertainment%20room.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Textron%20Aviation's%20family%20of%20Cessna%20CitationJet%20aircraft%20proved%20to%20be%20the%20most%20popular%20in%20the%20US%20last%20year%2C%20performing%20a%20collective%20273%2C522%20flights%20in%202023%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20aircraft-tracking%20website%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjetspy.com%2Fnews%2F2024%2F01%2F19%2F2023-us-business-jet-activity-report%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJetSpy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20the%20CitationJet%20series%2C%20which%20all%20offer%20varying%20ranges%2C%20speeds%2C%20and%20cabins%20to%20suit%20the%20needs%20of%20rich%20flyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETextron%20Aviation%20builds%20a%20series%20of%20light%20business%20aircraft%20known%20as%20the%20CitationJet%2C%20which%20falls%20under%20the%20larger%20Citation%20family%20of%20private%20planes.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cessna%20Citation%20M2%20flying%20over%20snowy%20mountains.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df69e36080194819fad93c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Cessna%20Citation%20M2.%3Cp%3ETextron%20Aviation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20light-class%20family%20of%20aircraft%2C%20also%20known%20as%20CJ%2C%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%201990s%20and%20has%20been%20a%20consistently%20popular%20option%20for%20the%20ultrawealthy%20due%20to%20the%20fleet's%20versatility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThere%20are%20four%20distinct%20models%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Citation%20M2%2C%20the%20CJ2%2C%20the%20CJ3%2C%20and%20the%20CJ4%20%E2%80%94%20which%20were%20developed%20after%20the%20company's%20Citation%201%20failed.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222801%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20headrest%20in%20a%20CJ3.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df6a2a6080194819fad990%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222101%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20cabin%20of%20a%20CJ3.%3Cp%3ETextron%20Aviation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECessna's%20series%20of%20CJ%20airplanes%20dominate%20the%20market%20share%20with%2051%25%2C%20followed%20by%20Embraer%20and%20Hawker%20aircraft%20at%2019%25%20and%2014%25%2C%20respectively%2C%20per%20JetSpy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20original%20Citation%201%20was%20discontinued%20due%20to%20its%20expensive%20engines.%20Still%2C%20Cessna%20saw%20a%20market%20need%20for%20a%20light%2C%20lower-cost%20private%20jet.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223688%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dutch%20Minister%20Van%20der%20Stoel%20leaves%20from%20Schipol%20for%20a%20trip%20to%20China%20and%20Japan%20in%201975.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df6aecce7f1785b2e4972f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222433%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDutch%20Minister%20Van%20der%20Stoel%20boards%20a%20Citation%201%20Jet%20at%20Schipol%20Amsterdam%20Airport%20for%20a%20trip%20to%20China%20and%20Japan%20in%201975.%3Cp%3ENationaal%20Archief%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Citation%201%20used%20Pratt%20%26amp%3B%20Whitney%20JT15D-1%20engines%2C%20which%20were%20expensive%20and%20made%20the%20jet%20uncompetitive.%20This%20caused%20the%20program%20to%20be%20canceled%20in%201985.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhen%20designing%20the%20CJ%2C%20Cessna%20settled%20on%20a%20new%20design%20that%20combined%20a%20lighter%20airframe%20with%20inexpensive%20but%20effective%20Williams%20FJ44%20engines.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20CJ4%2B%20aircraft%20on%20the%20runway.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df6be96080194819fadba8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20CJ4%20model.%3Cp%3ETextron%20Aviation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20model%20was%20unveiled%20in%201989%20and%20eventually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airliners.net%2Faircraft-data%2Fcessna-citationjet-cj1-cj2%2F159%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edelivered%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%201993%20to%20much%20fanfare%20as%20it%20outperformed%20the%20original%20Citation%201%20thanks%20to%20its%20favorable%20speed%2C%20size%2C%20and%20price%20point.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECessna%20eventually%20developed%20the%20original%20CJ%20into%20the%20four%20different%20CitationJet%20models%20through%20a%20series%20of%20operational%20and%20performance%20upgrades.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221777%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20CJ4%20cockpit.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df70e9ce7f1785b2e49c16%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20CJ4%20cockpit.%3Cp%3ETextron%20Aviation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECessna's%20CitationJet%20family%20is%20built%20upon%20the%20original%20design%20but%20learned%20from%20the%20mistakes%20of%20the%20Pratt%20%26amp%3B%20Whitney%20engines%20to%20create%20a%20more%20operationally%20favorable%20jet%20with%20a%20spacious%20and%20comfortable%20cabin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20improvements%20to%20the%20cockpit%20and%20cabin%20are%20visible%20in%20the%20current%20models%20coming%20off%20the%20assembly%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20smallest%20is%20the%20M2%2C%20which%20can%20fly%20about%201%2C784%20miles%20nonstop%20and%20has%20a%20list%20price%20of%20%244.7%20million.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20M2%20flying%20over%20green%20mountains.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df6d1a90413ab8e1d786bd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221848%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Citation%20M2%20version.%3Cp%3ETextron%20Aviation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20M2%2C%20which%20has%20more%20efficient%20Williams%20FJ44-1AP-21%20turbofans%20that%20propel%20it%20to%20about%20465%20mph%2C%20is%20still%20in%20production.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjetadvisors.com%2Fjet%2Fcitation-i%2Fperformance%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECitation%201%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20by%20comparison%2C%20could%20only%20fly%20up%20to%20about%20405%20mph.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20M2%20jet%20also%20has%20an%20upgraded%20cockpit%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faviationweek.com%2Fbusiness-aviation%2Foperators-survey-cessna-citation-m2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGarmin%20avionics%3C%2Fa%3E%20instead%20of%20those%20from%20Rockwell%20Collins%20and%20can%20climb%20faster%20and%20fly%20faster%20than%20its%20predecessor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAccording%20to%20Textron%2C%20the%20M2%20has%20a%20cabin%20height%20and%20width%20of%20five%20feet%20and%20a%20width%20of%2011%20feet.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221777%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22black%20and%20orange%20interior%20of%20M2.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df6d28ce7f1785b2e4993b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20interior%20of%20the%20M2%2C%20which%20typically%20fits%20six%20people%20in%20the%20main%20cabin.%3Cp%3ETextron%20Aviation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20the%20aircraft%20is%20not%20quite%20tall%20enough%20for%20an%20adult%20to%20stand%20upright%2C%20but%20it%20is%20still%20spacious%20and%20comfortable%20enough%20for%20businesspeople%20to%20choose%20it%20over%20other%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20typical%20M2%20configuration%20includes%20space%20for%20six%20people%20and%20features%20amenities%20like%20power%2C%20cupholders%2C%20and%20tables.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20iphone%20charging%20in%20the%20M2%20with%20a%20cupholder%20and%20USB%20in%20view.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df6d85ce7f1785b2e49975%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20CitationJet%20family%20of%20aircraft%20all%20feature%20the%20regular%20amenities%20of%20private%20jets%2C%20like%20cupholders%20and%20ample%20legroom.%3Cp%3ETextron%20Aviation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plane%20is%20certified%20for%20a%20single%20pilot%2C%20so%20it%20can%20actually%20fit%20up%20to%20seven%20people%20in%20total%20with%20the%20second%20pilot's%20seat%20open.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20most%20comfortably%20fits%20four%20or%20five.%20According%20to%20Textron%2C%20the%20fifth%20and%20sixth%20seats%20face%20sideways%20and%20are%20situated%20outside%20the%20main%20cabin%2C%20including%20one%20in%20the%20lavatory%20and%20one%20right%20in%20front%20of%20the%20exit%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAlthough%20not%20built%20anymore%2C%20Cessna%20developed%20a%20stretched%20version%20of%20the%20CJ1%20and%20called%20it%20the%20CJ2.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223864%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Centerline%20Cessna%20Citation%20CJ2%20business%20jet%20(G-OCJZ)%20taxiing%20on%20Manchester%20International%20Airport%20tarmac.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df6dbd6080194819fadd19%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222576%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Centerline%20Cessna%20Citation%20CJ2%20business%20jet%20taxiing%20at%20Manchester%20International%20Airport.%3Cp%3EJuha%20Remes%2FiStock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CJ2%20is%20five%20feet%20longer%20than%20the%20original%20CJ1%20and%20was%20first%20delivered%20in%202000.%20It%20can%20fly%20up%20to%20481%20mph%20across%20about%201%2C375%20miles%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbjtonline.com%2Faircraft%2Fcessna-citation-cj2-0%23%3A~%3Atext%3DCessna%2520Citation%2520CJ2%252B%2520Range%2520Map%2Cto%2520update%2520the%2520range%2520map.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Jet%20Traveler%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20CJ2%2B%20%26quot%3BAlpine%20Edition%26quot%3B%20is%20similar%20to%20the%20M2%20in%20its%20cabin%20and%20Garmin%20cockpit%2C%20but%20it%20had%20low%20demand%20and%20went%20out%20of%20production%20in%202016.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20CJ2%2B.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df6ee9ce7f1785b2e49a77%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Cessna%20CJ2%2B%20went%20out%20of%20production%2C%20leaving%20only%20the%20latest%20M2%2C%20CJ3%2B%2C%20and%20CJ4%2B%20models%20for%20sale%20new.%3Cp%3ETextron%20Aviation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20M2%20and%20CJ3%2B%20counterparts%20proved%20to%20be%20better%20suited%20for%20the%20market%20of%20the%20CJ2%20model%2C%20a%20company%20spokesperson%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.flyingmag.com%2Fcessna-citation-cj2-plus-no-longer-in-production%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFlying%20Magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20aircraft%20is%20still%20available%20to%20charter%20or%20buy%20used%2C%20though.%20The%20average%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aircraftcostcalculator.com%2FAircraftOperatingCosts%2F85%2FCessna%2BCitation%2BCJ2%2B%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epre-owned%20cost%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20about%20%244.5%20million%2C%20down%20from%20the%20original%20list%20price%20of%20%246.5%20million%20before%20production%20ended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAlthough%20the%20CJ2%2B%20model%20proved%20less%20popular%2C%20the%20third%20rendition%20of%20the%20jet%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%247.2%20million%20CJ3%20variant%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20success.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223870%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20stock%20photo%20of%20a%20white%20and%20red%20Cessna%20CJ3%2B.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df6f5590413ab8e1d78852%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222573%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Citation%20CJ3%2B%20is%20the%20third%20development%20from%20the%20original%20CJ1.%3Cp%3EMaikel%20de%20Vaan%2FiStock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcessna.txtav.com%2Fen%2Fcitation%2Fcj3-gen2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETextron%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20CJ3%2B%20features%20a%20Garmin%20cockpit%20with%20advanced%20handling%20and%20fuel%20burn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbjtonline.com%2Faircraft%2Fcessna-citation-cj3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECJ3%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20lighter%20and%20faster%20than%20the%20CJ2%20it%20was%20modeled%20after%20and%20is%20equipped%20with%20slightly%20better%20Williams%20turbofan%20engines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20cabin%20height%20and%20width%20are%20that%20of%20the%20M2%2C%20but%20with%20a%20nearly%2016-foot%20length%20that%20can%20comfortably%20fit%20eight%20seats.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Interior%20of%20Cessna%20CJ3%2B.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df6f9190413ab8e1d788ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20CJ3%2B%20has%20space%20for%20a%20third%20set%20of%20seats%20in%20the%20cabin.%3Cp%3ETextron%20Aviation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20configuration%20includes%20six%20seats%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bclub-style%26quot%3B%20arrangement.%20Textron%20offers%20the%20option%20to%20add%20up%20to%20two%20more%20seats%20in%20the%20main%20cabin%20or%20a%20%26quot%3Bcustom%20extended%20refreshment%20center%26quot%3B%20in%20lieu%20of%20one%20in%20the%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20aft%20lavatory%20can%20also%20be%20fitted%20with%20a%20vanity%2C%20if%20preferred%2C%20per%20Textron.%20The%20aircraft%20also%20has%20increased%20baggage%20space%20compared%20to%20the%20M2.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESimilar%20to%20the%20M2%20%E2%80%94%20and%20all%20CJ%20models%20for%20that%20matter%20%E2%80%94%20the%20CJ3%2B%20is%20certified%20for%20single-pilot%20operations.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222802%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22CJ3%2B%20Cockpit.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df6fd3ce7f1785b2e49b1e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222102%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20cockpit%20of%20the%20CJ3%2B.%3Cp%3ETextron%20Aviation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20one%20person%20can%20sit%20in%20the%20first%20officer's%20seat%2C%20bringing%20the%20total%20capacity%20to%20nine.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIntroduced%20in%202006%2C%20the%20largest%20of%20the%20CJ%20variants%20is%20the%20CJ4%2C%20which%20stretches%20about%20two%20feet%20longer%20than%20the%20CJ3%2B.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cessna%20CJ4%20flying%20over%20flat%20greenlands.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df70a06080194819fadfa8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Cessna%20CJ4%20has%20evolved%20into%20the%20CJ4%20Gen2.%3Cp%3ETextron%20Aviation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETextron%20has%20again%20kept%20the%20same%20cabin%20height