pointments%20and%20standards%20of%20conduct%3B%20(2)%20bring%20an%20objective%20view%20in%20the%20evaluation%20of%20the%20performance%20of%20the%20board%20and%20management%3B%20(3)%20scrutinise%20the%20performance%20of%20management%20in%20meeting%20agreed%20goals%20and%20objectives%20and%20monitor%20the%20reporting%20of%20performance%3B%20(4)%20satisfy%20themselves%20on%20the%20integrity%20of%20financial%20information%20and%20that%20financial%20controls%20and%20the%20systems%20of%20risk%20management%20are%20robust%20and%20defensible%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20%E2%80%98duties%E2%80%99%2C%20it%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhere%20they%20%5Bindependent%20directors%5D%20have%20concerns%20about%20the%20running%20of%20the%20company%20or%20a%20proposed%20action%2C%20ensure%20that%20these%20are%20addressed%20by%20the%20Board%20and%2C%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20they%20are%20not%20resolved%2C%20insist%20that%20their%20concerns%20are%20recorded%20in%20the%20minutes%20of%20the%20Board%20meeting%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20RBI%20documents%20various%20violations%20and%20penalises%20a%20bank%2C%20it%20should%20be%20taken%20extremely%20seriously%20by%20the%20board%20of%20directors.%20Typically%2C%20the%20Audit%20Committee%20%E2%80%93%20in%20which%20Vaibhav%20Goel%2C%20Manju%20Agarwal%20and%20Sairee%20Chahal%20were%20present%20as%20independent%20directors%2C%20and%20sometimes%20the%20Risk%20Management%20Committee%2C%20with%20Ramesh%20Abhishek%2C%20Manju%20Agarwal%20and%20Shinjini%20Kumar%20as%20independent%20directors%2C%20will%20examine%20the%20issues%20raised%20by%20RBI%20more%20closely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20board%20appoints%20a%20compliance%20officer%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20issues%20highlighted%20by%20the%20regulator%20are%20addressed.%20A%20time-bound%20compliance%20report%20has%20to%20be%20first%20submitted%20to%20the%20board%2C%20notifying%20that%20the%20bank%20has%20complied%20with%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20directive%20and%20addressed%20its%20concerns.%20This%20report%20is%20thereafter%20sent%20to%20the%20RBI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPaytm%20Payments%20Bank%E2%80%99s%20Audit%20and%20Risk%20Management%20Committee%20in%20FY23%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F28125204%2Fimage-1875.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22892%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F28125204%2Fimage-1875.png%20892w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F28125204%2Fimage-1875-300x105.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699264%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22311%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20the%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%E2%80%99s%20board%20of%20directors%2C%20including%20its%20independent%20directors%2C%20during%20this%20period%2C%20abjectly%20failed%20in%20carrying%20out%20their%20role%20and%20duties%20is%20evident%20from%20the%20public%20statements%20made%20by%20senior%20RBI%20officials%20after%20the%20regulator%20asked%20the%20bank%20to%20stop%20incremental%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERBI%20deputy%20governor%20Swaminathan%20J.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstartupstorymedia.com%2Finsights-deputy-governor-states-rbi-sanctions-paytm-payments-bank-for-non-compliance%2F%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20supervisory%20action%20on%20a%20regulated%20entity%20for%20persistent%20non-compliance.%20Such%20actions%20are%20invariably%20preceded%20by%20months%2C%20and%20at%20times%2C%20years%20of%20bilateral%20engagement%20where%20we%20not%20only%20point%20out%20deficiencies%20but%20provide%20more%20than%20adequate%20time%20to%20take%20corrective%20action.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%208%2C%202024%2C%20Shaktikanta%20Das%2C%20RBI%20governor%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Frbi-swaminathan-j-shaktikanta-das-paytm-payments-bank-ppbl-9150621%2F%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CSufficient%20time%20is%20given%20to%20non-compliant%20entities%20but%20action%20is%20taken%20when%20bilateral%20talks%20don%E2%80%99t%20yield%20action.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20shocking%20is%20that%20the%20board%20of%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%20had%20two%20experienced%20bankers%2C%20Shinjini%20Kumar%2C%20a%20former%20RBI%20official%20and%20also%20a%20former%20CEO%20of%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%2C%20and%20Manju%20Agarwal%2C%20a%20former%20senior%20executive%20of%20SBI.%20Both%20of%20them%20would%20have%20been%20familiar%20with%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20regulatory%20and%20supervisory%20procedures%2C%20as%20well%20as%20KYC%20norms%20for%20banks.%20Yet%2C%20despite%20their%20presence%2C%20the%20bank%20was%20unable%20to%20satisfy%20the%20regulator%E2%80%99s%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20their%20expertise%20and%20experience%2C%20many%20independent%20directors%20are%20selected%20for%20their%20lack%20of%20spine%20in%20protecting%20non-promoter%20interests.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20founders%2C%20professional%20management%20prefers%20individuals%20who%20do%20not%20grill%20the%20management%2C%20and%20quietly%20acquiesce%20to%20decisions%20which%20may%20be%20adverse%20to%20minority%2Fpublic%20interests.%20The%20conduct%20of%20independent%20directors%20ensures%20not%20only%20the%20extension%20of%20their%20terms%20with%20the%20support%20of%20the%20promoter%2Fmanagement%20but%20also%20qualifies%20them%20eminently%20to%20serve%20on%20the%20boards%20of%20other%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENormally%20independent%20directors%20consist%20of%20chartered%20accountants%20and%20lawyers%20whose%20business%20interests%20are%20intertwined%20with%20the%20corporate%20world%2C%2