election-case-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump's%20claims%20that%20he's%20immune%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20prosecution%20on%20charges%20that%20he%20conspired%20to%20overturn%20the%202020%20election%20results.%20The%20court%20said%20it%20would%20hear%20arguments%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20end%20of%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-january-6-criminal-indictment-charges-explained-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efaces%20four%20federal%20charges%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20case%20related%20to%20his%20efforts%20to%20overturn%20the%202020%20presidential%20election.%20The%20special%20counsel%20Jack%20Smith's%20federal%20case%20against%20Trump%20cannot%20proceed%20until%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20makes%20its%20decision%2C%20which%20could%20take%20months.%20Trump%20has%20denied%20any%20wrongdoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20Trump%20can%20win%20even%20if%20he%20loses%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELegal%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20while%20the%20court's%20timeline%20for%20hearing%20Trump's%20claims%20was%20faster%20than%20usual%2C%20SCOTUS's%20involvement%20in%20the%20matter%20would%20further%20delay%20a%20possible%20trial%2C%20most%20likely%20buying%20Trump%20time%20until%20after%20the%202024%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20Trump%20loses%20on%20the%20immunity%20claim%2C%20he%20fundamentally%20still%20wins%20because%20he%20manages%20to%20avoid%20a%20trial%20before%20the%20election%2C%26quot%3B%20Scott%20Lemieux%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Washington%20who's%20an%20expert%20in%20constitutional%20law%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKenneth%20White%2C%20a%20former%20federal%20prosecutor%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20a%20decision%20from%20SCOTUS%20alone%20would%20take%20at%20least%20several%20months%20%E2%80%94%20possibly%20until%20the%20end%20of%20June%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20if%20the%20court%20determines%20Trump%20%3Cem%3Edoes%20not%3C%2Fem%3E%20have%20legal%20immunity%2C%20it%20would%20be%20at%20least%20another%20several%20months%20before%20the%20former%20president%20stood%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20guarantee%20that%20he%20will%20succeed%20in%20pushing%20the%20events%20until%20after%20the%20election%2C%20but%20it%20is%20certainly%20a%20big%20step%20in%20that%20direction%2C%26quot%3B%20White%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJustin%20Crowe%2C%20a%20SCOTUS%20expert%20who's%20a%20political-science%20professor%20at%20Williams%20College%2C%20concurred%20with%20White%20in%20an%20email%20to%20BI%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20benefit%20to%20Trump%20%26quot%3Bis%20entirely%20about%20timing%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20if%20the%20court%20ultimately%20rejects%20Trump's%20immunity%20claims%2C%20%26quot%3Bpreparations%20for%20the%20trial%20could%20not%20restart%20in%20earnest%20until%20late%20June%20or%20early%20July.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20say%20when%20the%20actual%20trial%20might%20then%20be%20able%20to%20start%2C%20but%20it%20becomes%20more%20and%20more%20likely%20that%20it%20wouldn't%20be%20completed%20by%20the%20election%2C%26quot%3B%20Crowe%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%20Krissoff%2C%20a%20former%20federal%20prosecutor%20in%20New%20York%2C%20said%20Trump's%20primary%20legal%20approach%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-criminal-cases-ranked-how-much-legal-trouble-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efour%20criminal%20cases%3C%2Fa%3E%20he%20faces%20had%20been%20to%20delay%2C%20delay%2C%20delay.%20(He%20has%20denied%20wrongdoing%20and%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20in%20the%20cases.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20legal%20experts%20assume%20Trump%20is%20trying%20to%20push%20his%20legal%20entanglements%20until%20after%20the%20election%20with%20the%20hopes%20that%20he%20can%20dismiss%20the%20federal%20charges%20against%20him%20or%20pardon%20himself%20from%20the%20crimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Trump%20is%20elected%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20very%20unlikely%20that%20Jack%20Smith's%20cases%20continue%20just%20because%20of%20the%20control%20Trump%20will%20have%20over%20the%20Justice%20Department%2C%26quot%3B%20Krissoff%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-key-cases-civil-criminal-investigations-lawsuits-updates-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelection-interference%20case%20and%20the%20classified-documents%20case%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoron%20Kalir%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Cleveland%20State%20University%20College%20of%20Law%20with%20expertise%20in%20statutory%20interpretation%2C%20agreed%20that%20in%20terms%20of%20timing%2C%20this%20was%20a%20big%20win%20for%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20did%20succeed%20in%20the%20most%20important%20task%20of%20all%2C%20and%20that%20is%20not%20to%20have%20a%20trial%20before%20the%20election%2C%26quot%3B%20Kalir%20said%2C%20expressing%20his%20confidence%20that%20under%20this%20timeline%2C%20the%20chances%20of%20a%20trial%20before%20November%20were%20incredibly%20small.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20that%20while%20some%20might%20blame%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20the%20timing%2C%20one%20could%20argue%20the%20attorney%20general%20and%20Smith%20dragged%20their%20feet%20in%20actually%20bringing%20the%20charges%20against%20Trump%2C%20which%20were%20filed%20more%20than%20two%20years%20after%20the%20Capitol%20riot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20was%20a%20race%20against%20time%20Jack%20Smith%20had%2C%20and%20I%20think%20he%20lost%2C%26quot%3B%20Kalir%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Smith's%20office%20didn't%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%20Smith's%20office%20attempted%20to%20fast-track%20the%20question%20of%20presidential%20immunity%20last%20year.%20SCOTUS%20declined%20to%20hear%20the%20case%20in%20December%20of%202023%2C%20sending%20it%20to%20the%20appeals%20court%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWill%20SCOTUS%20rule%20in%20Trump's%20favor%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECarolyn%20Shapiro%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Chicago-Kent's%20Institute%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20told%20BI%20the%20high%20court's%20agreement%20to%20review%20the%20case%20at%20all%20was%20a%20win%20for%20Trump%20because%20%26quot%3Bit%20suggests%20that%20there%20are%20at%20least%20some%20justices%20taking%20his%20position%20seriously%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bastonishing%26quot%3B%20because%20Trump's%20claim%20%26quot%3Bis%20so%20antithetical%20to%20our%20constitutional%20order.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20with%20a%206-3%20conservative%20tilt%2C%20the%20court%20is%20unlikely%20to%20grant%20Trump%20carte-blanche%20presidential%20immunity%2C%20several%20other%20legal%20experts%20have%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKalir%20said%20the%20fact%20that%20SCOTUS%20took%20up%20the%20case%20didn't%20suggest%20it%20was%20considering%20ruling%20in%20Trump's%20favor.%20Rather%2C%20he%20said%20it%20spoke%20more%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bmomentous%26quot%3B%20nature%20of%20the%20case%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20court%20hadn't%20faced%20a%20case%20like%20this%20in%20its%20234-year%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20really%20a%20first-of-its-kind%20set%20of%20constitutional%20questions%20that%20the%20court%20never%20dealt%20with%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20one%20of%20those%20seminal%20cases%20that%20the%20court%20would%20not%20pass%20over%20the%20opportunity%20to%20speak%20about.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKalir%2C%20who's%20pretty%20confident%20the%20court%20will%20not%20grant%20Trump%20immunity%2C%20said%20it%20largely%20came%20down%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaw-professor-grades-trump-lawyer-immunity-argument-assassinate-political-rival-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegal%20argument%20in%20favor%20of%20absolute%20immunity%3C%2Fa%3E%20being%20meritless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20nine%20justices%20%E2%80%94%20three%20of%20whom%20were%20appointed%20to%20the%20court%20by%20Trump%20himself%20%E2%80%94%20had%20also%20not%20consistently%20delivered%20legal%20wins%20on%20Trump's%20behalf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20conservative%20court%2C%20but%20it%20hasn't%20been%20a%20reliably%20Trump-obedient%20conservative%20court%2C%26quot%3B%20White%20said.%20%26quot%3BTo%20a%20large%20extent%2C%20they%20rebuffed%20his%20efforts%20to%20use%20them%20to%20back%20up%20the%20challenge%20to%20the%202020%20elections%2C%20and%20they%20haven't%20gone%20for%20his%20most%20crazy%20stuff.%20I%20don't%20think%20he%20can%20count%20on%20that.%20But%20never%20say%20never.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKrissoff%20added%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20likely%20to%20issue%20as%20narrow%20a%20ruling%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20not%20a%20body%20inclined%20to%20make%20broad%2C%20sweeping%20decisions%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20there's%20a%20narrow%20way%20through%20a%20case%2C%20they'll%20take%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-will-soctus-rule-on-trump-presidential-immunity-claim-experts-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709176286000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657758f758e7c0c29a2bbd8b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-will-soctus-rule-on-trump-presidential-immunity-claim-experts-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Trump%20could%20benefit%20from%20SCOTUS's%20hearing%20of%20his%20presidential-immunity%20claims%20by%20delaying%20a%20trial.%20Experts%20say%20it's%20unlikely%20the%20court%20will%20side%20with%20Trump.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lloydlee%40insider.com%20(Lloyd%20Lee%2CErin%20Snodgrass%2CKelsey%20Vlamis)%22%2C%22en